interferometer/channel/name.documentation: Short string identifier (unique for a given device)

interferometer/channel/description.documentation: Description, e.g. “channel viewing the upper divertor”

interferometer/channel/line_of_sight.documentation: Description of the line of sight of the channel, defined by two points when the beam is not reflected, a third point is added to define the reflected beam path

interferometer/channel/line_of_sight/fir.documentation: Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

interferometer/channel/line_of_sight/sec.documentation: Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

interferometer/channel/line_of_sight/thi.documentation: Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

interferometer/channel/wavelength.documentation: Set of wavelengths used for interferometry

interferometer/channel/wavelength/phase_.documentation: Phase measured for this wavelength, corrected from fringe jumps

interferometer/channel/wavelength/fringe.documentation: Signed number of 2pi phase corrections applied to remove a fringe jump, for each time slice on which a correction has been made
List of time slices of the pulse on which a fringe jump correction has been made

interferometer/channel/wavelength/phase_.documentation: Conversion factor to be used to convert phase into line density for this wavelength

interferometer/channel/path_length_varia.documentation: Optical path length variation due to the plasma

interferometer/channel/n_e_line.documentation: Line integrated density, possibly obtained by a combination of multiple interferometry wavelengths. Corresponds to the density integrated along the full line-of-sight (i.e. forward AND return for a reflected channel: NO dividing by 2 correction)

interferometer/channel/n_e_line/validity.documentation: Indicator of the validity of the data for each time slice. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

Indicator of the validity of the data for the whole acquisition period. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

interferometer/channel/n_e_line_average.documentation: Line average density inferred from interferometer measurements. Corresponds to the density integrated along the full line-of-sight and then divided by the length of the line-of-sight

interferometer/channel/n_e_line_average/.documentation: Indicator of the validity of the data for each time slice. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

Indicator of the validity of the data for the whole acquisition period. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

interferometer/channel/n_e.documentation: Estimated electron density profile on a set of positions along the line of sight and used by forward models.

interferometer/channel/n_e/positions.documentation: Positions along the line of sight

interferometer/channel/n_e/positions/phi.documentation: Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

interferometer/n_e_volume_average.documentation: Volume average plasma density estimated from the line densities measured by the various channels

interferometer/n_e_volume_average/validi.documentation: Indicator of the validity of the data for each time slice. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

Indicator of the validity of the data for the whole acquisition period. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

interferometer/electrons_n.documentation: Total number of electrons in the plasma, estimated from the line densities measured by the various channels

interferometer/electrons_n/validity_time.documentation: Indicator of the validity of the data for each time slice. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

interferometer/electrons_n/validity.documentation: Indicator of the validity of the data for the whole acquisition period. 0: valid from automated processing, 1: valid and certified by the diagnostic RO; - 1 means problem identified in the data processing (request verification by the diagnostic RO), -2: invalid data, should not be used (values lower than -2 have a code-specific meaning detailing the origin of their invalidity)

interferometer/latency.documentation: Upper bound of the delay between physical information received by the detector and data available on the real-time (RT) network.
